<li>Curli and extracellular matrix synthesis involves a complex regulatory network that is dependent on the CsgD ( AgfD ) regulator .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=11489123" target="_blank">11489123</a>]<br></li>
<li>At the centre of this network is the CsgD protein , an essential positive regulator of the csgBA genes , whose synthesis is upregulated by regulatory feed-forward cascades under control of RpoS ( sS ) , the master regulator of the general stress response ( Hengge-Aronis , 2002 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=22250746" target="_blank">22250746</a>]<br></li>
<li>If this is the case , the set of genes under the control of the CsgD global regulator must be activated in the presence of MlrA overexpression .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20874755" target="_blank">20874755</a>]<br></li>
<li>Reflecting such situations in nature , the promoter for the master regulator CsgD is under the control of a number of transcription factors .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=20466769" target="_blank">20466769</a>]<br></li>
<li>CsgD , the master transcription regulator of curli biogenesis , similarly is under the control of multiple sRNAs ( OmrA , OmrB , McaS , RprA , and GcvB ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=23666921" target="_blank">23666921</a>]<br></li>
<li>For comparison , we also included various regulatory mutants in the analysis : mutations in any of the components of the sS-MlrA-CsgD regulatory cascade that controls curli and cellulose-synthesis , strongly reduced or eliminated Congo red binding .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17010156" target="_blank">17010156</a>]<br></li>
