				<div class="SIT"><br><ul><li>Strains , plasmids , and primers used in this study Strain , plamid or primer Reference or source Relevant genotype or characteristics E. coli Reference strain MG1655 csgA : : uidA-kan MG1655 PHL856 LG20 Brombacher et al. ( 2006 ) Prigent-Combaret et al. ( 2001 ) This work MG1655 crl : : 920cam ; obtained by transduction from LP468 ( Pratt & Silhavy , 1998 ) MG1655 DbcsA : : kan ; obtained by P1vir transduction LG26 This work from MG1655bcsA ( gift from C. Beloin ) Plasmids pT7-7 Control vector , ampicillin resistance , T7 RNA polymerase-dependent promoter csgD gene cloned into plasmid pT7-7 as a 651 bp NdeI/PstI fragment Control vector allowing direct cloning of PCR S. Tabor , Institute of Cancer Research , London , UK Prigent-Combaret et al. ( 2001 ) pT7CsgD Invitrogen pTOPO products , ampicillin and kanamycin resistance adrA gene cloned as PCR product into pTOPO vector Sequence CATAATTGGTCAAGCTGGGACTAA GCAACAACCGCCAAAAGTTT This work Utilization pTOPOAdrA Primers RT-PCR experiments RT-PCR experiments RT-PCR experiments GGCTGGGTCAGCTACCAG CGTCGGTTATACACGCCCG GACGCTGGTGGCGCTG GGGCCGCGAGATCACC GCTCCGTCTCTATAATTTGGG RT-PCR experiments RT-PCR experiments RT-PCR experiments adrA cloning adrA cloning ATCCTGATGACTTTCGCCGG WT csgA Dbcs ( a ) 20 15 To determine cell aggregation , 2 ml cultures were grown overnight in 15 ml Falcon tubes with vigorous shaking , then left standing at room temperature for 1 h. Cell aggregation was determined by visual estimation of the cell sediment at the bottom of the Falcon tube .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=18599830" target="_blank">18599830</a>]<br></li>
<li>For construction of the CsgD expression plasmid pCsgD for CsgD puriﬁcation , a DNA fragment corresponding to the csgD coding region was ampliﬁed by PCR using E. coli KP7600 genome DNA as a template and a pair of primers , TF030S ( 5 - TAACGTTTCAGCGGCCGCTCGCCTGAGGTT-3 ) and TF030T ( 5 - GC GGGGTTTCCATATGTTTAATGAAGTCCA-3 ) , and after digestion with NdeI and NotI , cloned into pET21a ( ) ( Novagen ) at the corresponding sites .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=21421764" target="_blank">21421764</a>]<br></li>
